observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require:

The concerned MHO personnel to submit immediately to the audit team, thru the Accountant, the following documents to establish their claim to OCA:

Office Order or equivalent from the LCE or his authorized representative requiring the personnel (regular, contractual, or on a job order) to report for work to the health facilities involved in the COVID-19 response, especially the BHWs and personnel from other departments;

Daily Time Records with Biometric printouts or copies of logbook or Certificate of Attendance in the health facilities involved in COVID-19 response by their immediate supervisor during the period of claims; 

Certification by the Municipal Health Officer, or his/her authorized representative of the number of hours that the HCWs and non-HCWs physically report for work in a month;

detailed computation of OCA prepared by the LGU, which was validated by the DOH-CHD and noted by the PHO Officer; and

Memorandum of Agreement and Resolution authorizing the LCE to enter into a MOA with the DOH.

Xxx.

We recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Human Resource Management Officer to: 

Prepare the Organizational Structure and Staffing Pattern Plan in order to assess the required number of JO workers to be hired based on necessity and financial capability of the Municipality;

Consider filling up vacant positions under Plantilla to minimize the number of JO workers to be hired;

Xxx

We recommended and the Management agreed to:

Require the Municipal Accountant to ensure that received, issued and balance of COVID-19 vaccines are disclose in the Notes Financial Statements; and

Require the Property Custodian to:

Use the Acknowledge Receipt for In-Kind Donations for DRRM and Issuance form for In-Kind Donations-DRRM for the receipt and issuance of COVID-19 vaccines;

Prepare and maintain the Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM and Inventory Report-DRRM for the receipt and utilization of COVID-19 Vaccines;

Prepare and submit to Office of the Civil Defense (OCD), Auditor of the OCD and to COA Auditor, the Monthly Report on the Receipt and Distribution/Issuance of Donated Relief Goods for the received COVID-19 vaccines;

Prepare and submit the monthly Inventory List of Items for DRRM supported with the required documents to COA and to Municipal Accounting Office.

We recommended that the Management:

Allocate funds for Disaster Recovery and Rehabilitation areas as this is also important in disaster and risk management;

Xxx

We recommended that the LCE:
direct the Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Municipal Social Welfare and Development Officer (MSWDO) to submit the duly accomplished SAC Forms, printed copies of properly labeled pictures of the beneficiaries during actual receipt of the assistance, explanation/authorization from the DSWD that barangay clearance, voters certification and live birth were allowed to be submitted in lieu of valid IDs;
require the Municipal Treasurer, the MSWDO, and the Punong Barangay/Barangay Chairmen concerned to submit an explanation on the process of identifying the beneficiaries and replacements, and documents supporting the time extension asked from the DSWD for the distribution of ESP-SAP;
instruct the MSWDO to: 1) correct errors in the encoded SAC Forms as to SAC codes, misspelled names of beneficiaries, and residence (barangay); 2) submit explanation on the inclusion of five beneficiaries who are 4Ps beneficiaries; and 3) submit information on the status of the returned cash assistance.
order the posting of the list of beneficiaries who already received the emergency subsidy in the Municipality’s official website, social media accounts, and at conspicuous places of the municipality.
